\id INT - Odoodee
\periph Bible Introduction
\mt2 Preface
\p This book contains the following New Testament books, translated into the Odoodee language: Matthew, Mark, Luke, John, Acts, Romans, 1 & 2 Thessalonians, 1 & 2 Timothy, Titus, Philemon, James, 1,2,3 John and Jude.
\p All Scripture is inspired by God and is useful for teaching the truth, rebuking error, correcting faults, and giving instruction for right living, so that the person who serves God may be fully qualified and equipped to do every kind of good deed. (2 Tim 3:16-17)
\p We pray that God, through the Word of His grace, will build up the faith of the Odoodee people.
\mt2 To daga malalo
\p Booka toowa hagee ma kulodu booka pepuso hagee moloso: Matiyu, Maka, Luka, Yonee, Diye di odoo, Loum, 1 & 2 Tesalonika, 1 & 2 Timoti, Taites, Palimon, Yemes, 1,2,3 Yonee, osoloso Yuda.
\p Godeeyo to booka mapoo hogugu susuga ee Godee maga simi. Esiga Godeeyo to booka mapoo hogugu goo oso odoo mapoo tei goo eligilone, edebeeyo dooboo dagaduga, tei goo eligi mapoo ka ido sibo domoloso. Osoloso Godeeyo to booka mapoo hogugu goo oso edebeeyo tekepo badeli goo ee eligiliso, Godeeyo odoo oso mopoodoo doloso goo tekepo susuga tomo silesibilei ee tebilame. (2 Timoti 3:16-17)
\p Iyo Godee mapoo takooso, Godeeye yayo sooloo dolone pidili to tekepo maga nibada tei too goo ee kibilame. 
